value.value: any structural anomaly of the connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of corneal stroma that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity
ヒスチンの血中濃度異常
the amount of the amino acid histidine in the blood is more or less than expected
ヒスチジン血中濃度上昇
the amount of the amino acid histidine in the blood is more than expected
ヒスチジン血中濃度低下
the amount of the amino acid histidine in the blood is less than expected
ヒスチジン尿症
increased excretion of histidine and related imidazole metabolites in urine
全身動脈形態異常
any structural anomaly of the arteries that carry oxygenated blood away from the heart to the body, as opposed to the pulmonary arteries, which carry deoxygenated blood to the lungs
冠状動静脈瘻
an abnormal communication between the terminus of a coronary artery, bypassing the myocardial capillary bed and entering any segment of the systemic or pulmonary circulation
冠状動脈心腔瘻
an abnormal communication between the terminus of a coronary artery, bypassing the myocardial capillary bed and entering a chamber of the heart (coronary-cameral fistula)
大動脈弓離断、a型
complete discontinuation/blockage between the ascending and descending aorta with the interruption located distal to the subclavian artery that is ipsilateral to the second carotid artery
大動脈弓離断、b型
complete discontinuation/blockage between the ascending and descending aorta with the interruption located between second carotid artery and ipsilateral subclavian artery
異所性心臓、心臓転位
congenital condition in which the heart is exposed and/or protruding from the thorax due to abnormal development of the sternum, pericardium and/or the abdominal wall
総動脈幹遺残、type 1

complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; type i is characterized by origin of a single pulmonary trunk from the left lateral aspect of the common trunk, with branching of the left and right pulmonary arteries from the pulmonary trunk
総動脈幹遺残、type 2

complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; type II is characterized by separate but proximate origins of the left and right pulmonary arterial branches from the posterolateral aspect of the common arterial trunk
総動脈幹遺残、type 3

complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; in type iii the branch pulmonary arteries originate independently from the common arterial trunk or aortic arch, most often from the left and right lateral aspects of the trunk; this occasionally occurs with origin of one pulmonary artery from the underside of the aortic arch, usually from a ductus arteriosus
総動脈幹遺残、type 4

complete failure of the common arterial trunk opening out of both ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development; type i is a form of the lesion with neither pulmonary arterial branch arises from the common trunk, and is more commonly recognized to be a form of pulmonary atresia with ventricular septal defect rather than truncus arteriosus

value.value: dループ大血管転位

value.value: complete transposition of the great arteries; the d- refers to the dextroposition of the bulboventricular loop (ie, the position of the right ventricle, which is on the right side); in addition, the aorta also tends to be on the right and anterior, and the great arteries are parallel rather than crossing

label.value: double outlet right ventricle, ventricular defect committed to aorta

value.value: a form of DORV in which blood from the left ventricle passes through a ventricular septal defect to the pulmonary artery, and blood from the right ventricle is directed to the aorta

label.value: double outlet right ventricle, doubly committed ventricular septal defect

value.value: 両大血管右室起始症、doubly committed型心室中隔欠損

label.value: double outlet right ventricle, noncommitted ventricular septal defect

value.value: 両大血管右室起始症、noncommitted型心室中隔欠損

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: double outlet right ventricle, noncommitted ventricular septal defect

value.value: a form of DORV in which the ventricular septal defect is distant from both the aorta and pulmonary artery and blood mixes in the right ventricle before entering these vessels, with the majority of deoxygenated blood entering the aorta
完全な共通房室管の均衡

a balanced complete atrioventricular septal defect occurs when the atrioventricular junction is connected equally to the right and left ventricles so that each ventricle receives a similar amount of blood and the ventricles are symmetrical in size

value.value: 完全な房室管の不均衡、左優性

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: unbalanced complete atrioventricular canal, left dominant

完全な共通房室管の不均衡

an unbalanced complete atrioventricular septal defect occurs when the atrioventricular junction is predominantly committed to either the right or left ventricle, leading to hypoplasia of the opposing ventricle receiving the smaller amount of blood
